            <h2>What are the different types of men&rsquo;s scarves?</h2>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ce-mobile-full ce-mobile-collapse">
        <div class="large-11 small-12 large-centered column">
            <img class="ceg-b32" src="//assets.macysassets.com/dyn_img/creativepages/Q8060009-108-02.jpg" alt="What are the different types of men's scarves?">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ceg-t35">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><p><strong>REVERSIBLE SCARVES</strong><br>Double the style! Get the look of two scarves in one with a reversible scarf. Make your mark with two types of plaid or keep it basic with solids. Want a cozier feel? Check out scarves made of wool. What color should you get? Stand out with a blue or red scarf, or blend in with neutrals like tan or grey. Warm up to reversible scarves from your favorite brands, like Polo Ralph Lauren and Alfani.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>CASHMERE SCARVES</strong><br>How do you luxe up your cold-weather look? Wrap up your winter wardrobe with a cashmere scarf for an elevated finish. How do you add a stylish statement to your overcoats? Select a cashmere scarf in a vibrant color to offset the neutral hue of your coat. Not only is cashmere fashionable, it&rsquo;s also a breathable fabric that will keep you warm this winter. Take your winter style to the next level with a cashmere scarf from Club Room or Polo Ralph Lauren.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>PRINTED SCARVES</strong><br>Do you want to liven up your fall/winter look? A printed scarf is a perfect solution to shake up your coats and jackets. Looking to keep things classic? Add some color with a plaid scarf in windowpane or buffalo checkered patterns. Not mad about plaid? Stand out in a striped scarf.  Want a trending look? Sport a logo scarf for a fashionable finish. Need a hat, too? Check out printed hat and scarf sets to make life easier. Personalize your cold-weather style with printed scarves rom Polo Ralph Lauren, Tommy Hilfiger and Calvin Klein.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>WATER-RESISTANT SCARVES</strong><br>Are you worried about your scarf getting wet? Stay drier in storms with a water-resistant scarf. Are you allergic to wool? Water-resistant scarfs are hypoallergenic and made of acrylic. Looking for a luxe feel without breaking the bank? Score V. Fraas&rsquo;s water-resistant Cashmink scarf that has the feel of cashmere without the excessive cost. A classic plaid scarf will lend a distinguished feel to your style. Shop the latest water-resistant men&rsquo;s scarves at Macy&rsquo;s.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="large-11 small-11 large-centered small-centered column">
            <h2>How to tie a scarf?</h2>
            <p class="ceg-b32">Once you have selected the right scarf, lend a finished feel to your look with the perfect knot. Below is a guide on how to tie a knot for every occasion, from the workweek to the weekend.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ce-mobile-full ce-mobile-collapse">
        <div class="large-11 small-12 large-centered column">
            <img class="ceg-b32" src="//assets.macysassets.com/dyn_img/creativepages/Q8060009-108-03.jpg" alt="How to tie a scarf?">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row ceg-t35">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><p><strong>THE PARISIAN</strong><br>Infuse a polished feel to all your jackets and coats with the Parisian knot. First, fold the scarf in half and place it around your neck. Then, guide the loose side through the loop generated by the fold. And voilà—a distinguished look!</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>THE ONE AROUND</strong><br>How do you tie together a casual outfit? Lay the scarf around your neck with one end slightly longer than the other. Drape the long end of the scarf around your neck once. You can totally play with the length for a personalized look.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>THE DRAPE</strong><br>How do you style a scarf with your suit jacket or overcoat? Simply drape the scarf over your shoulders, and then tuck the ends inside your jacket or coat. You&rsquo;ll be ready for your interview or dinner in high style!</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>THE OVERHAND</strong><br>Layer on instant sophistication to your style with an overhand knot. Place the scarf around your neck, so that both sides are facing forward. Next, wrap one end of the scarf over and then under the other side. Finally, drape the front side over the back end. Adjust the length to your preference for a unique look.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>THE WRAP AROUND</strong><br>Want a casual feel for your denim and bomber jackets? Lay the scarf around your neck with one end substantially longer than the other. Keep the short end of the scarf close to your neck. Then, wrap the long end of the scarf around your neck until it is short. Finally, tuck in both ends of the scarf for a laid-back feel.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
